JOHANNESBURG – Prince Harry and Meghan Markle will have their wedding in May 2018. The couple, who announced their engagement on Monday, will marry at St George's Chapel, Windsor Castle. WATCH: The stars were aligned when I met Meghan, says Harry The Kensington Palace Twitter page confirmed that Queen has given permission for the wedding to take place at the chapel. Harry (33), currently fifth-in-line to the British throne, and Markle (36), best known for her role in the US TV legal drama "Suits", became engaged earlier this month, the statement issued by Clarence House said. eNCA